  <amendments/>
  <summary>8/4/1995--Introduced.
Urges: (1) prompt implementation by the Government of Cameroon of postponed steps to promote further democratization in that country; (2) such Government to undertake measures to address human rights abuses; and (3) such Government and Cameroonian political parties to cease violence among ethnic groups and against foreign nationals. Commends the Administration for steps taken in support of democracy and human rights in Cameroon, and urges the Administration to explore additional measures to promote improved human rights and restoration of full democratic rule.</summary>
